Medicare & Medicaid = WHO provides coverage. They are types of health plans that provide insurance coverage
HMO / PPO / POS = HOW coverage is structured. These describe how the coverage works, not who provides it

21. Billed Amount
Definition: The total amount the provider charges for a service rendered to the member.

22. Allowed Amount
Definition: The maximum amount the health plan will recognize and pay for a service according to the contracted rate with the provider.
The member and health plan together never pay more than this amount.

23. Net Amount
Net Amount is the final amount the health plan or IPA actually pays to the provider for a claim.

Assume:
Billed Amount = $1,000
Allowed Amount = $600
Copay = $50
Deductible = $300
Coinsurance = $50
Step 1: Calculate Total Member Responsibility
$50 (copay) + $300 (deductible) + $50 (coinsurance) = $400
Step 2: Net Amount Paid by Plan / IPA
Allowed Amount = $600
Member pays $400
Net Amount = $600 ‚àí $400 = $200

